pan class="sr-blog-body"><span style="font-family:var(--sr-font-display);font-weight:500;font-size:26px">How much your site weighs on the environment (and on your wallet)</span><span style="font-size:15.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio)">Every visit consumes energy and produces CO₂. How to measure a website’s environmental impact, why light also means fast and cheap, and what the CSRD has to do with it.</span></span></a><a href="/en/blog/accessibility-statement-guide-2026/" class="sr-blog-row" data-cat="norme" style="color:inherit"><span class="sr-blog-date">16 JUL 2026</span><span class="sr-blog-body"><span style="font-family:var(--sr-font-display);font-weight:500;font-size:26px">Accessibility statement: a practical 2026 guide</span><span style="font-size:15.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio)">It’s the document the law requires, and without which an accessible site isn’t compliant. What the accessibility statement is, what it must contain and the mistakes to avoid.</span></span></a><a href="/en/blog/eaa-ecommerce-risks/" class="sr-blog-row" data-cat="norme" style="color:inherit"><span class="sr-blog-date">15 JUL 2026</span><span class="sr-blog-body"><span style="font-family:var(--sr-font-display);font-weight:500;font-size:26px">EAA 2026: what your e-commerce site really risks</span><span style="font-size:15.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio)">Since 28 June 2025 accessibility is a legal requirement, with fines up to 5% of revenue. Who’s covered, who’s exempt, and where to start — without the scaremongering.</span></span></a><a href="/en/blog/llms-txt-explained/" class="sr-blog-row" data-cat="seo" style="color:inherit"><span class="sr-blog-date">15 JUL 2026</span><span class="sr-blog-body"><span style="font-family:var(--sr-font-display);font-weight:500;font-size:26px">llms.txt: what it is, and does your site actually need it?</span><span style="font-size:15.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio)">A text file that explains your site to AI models, the way robots.txt does for Google. What it is, how to write it, and how much it really matters — no hype.</span></span></a><a href="/en/blog/get-cited-by-chatgpt-geo/" class="sr-blog-row" data-cat="seo" style="color:inherit"><span class="sr-blog-date">15 JUL 2026</span><span class="sr-blog-body"><span style="font-family:var(--sr-font-display);font-weight:500;font-size:26px">How to get found (and cited) by ChatGPT: a GEO guide</span><span style="font-size:15.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio)">More and more people ask ChatGPT instead of Google. GEO is the craft of getting cited in generated answers: what changes from SEO, and what to do about it.</span></span></a><a href="/en/blog/website-checkup-7-metrics/" class="sr-blog-row" data-cat="prestazioni" style="color:inherit"><span class="sr-blog-date">15 JUL 2026</span><span class="sr-blog-body"><span style="font-family:var(--sr-font-display);font-weight:500;font-size:26px">Website check-up: the 7 metrics that matter</span><span style="font-size:15.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio)">Whether a site is “doing well” or “doing badly” isn’t decided by gut feeling. There are seven metrics that tell its health — and a way to read them in a minute, for free.</span></span></a><a href="/en/blog/eeat-how-google-judges-credibility/" class="sr-blog-row" data-cat="seo" style="color:inherit"><span class="sr-blog-date">15 JUL 2026</span><span class="sr-blog-body"><span style="font-family:var(--sr-font-display);font-weight:500;font-size:26px">E-E-A-T: how Google judges your credibility</span><span style="font-size:15.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio)">Experience, expertise, authoritativeness, trust: the framework Google uses to judge who to rely on. What E-E-A-T is and how to strengthen it, no tricks.</span></span></a><a href="/en/blog/ecommerce-cost-italy-2026/" class="sr-blog-row" data-cat="decisioni" style="color:inherit"><span class="sr-blog-date">13 JUL 2026</span><span class="sr-blog-body"><span style="font-family:var(--sr-font-display);font-weight:500;font-size:26px">What an e-commerce site costs in Italy